# Commit message format

When generating commit messages (including via the Source Control sparkle button), always use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>
```

- **Types**: feat, fix, docs, chore, refactor, test, style
- **Scope**: optional (e.g. deps, api, auth)
- **Description**: imperative mood, max ~50 chars ("add" not "added")

Examples:
- `chore(deps): upgrade eslint and prettier`
- `feat: add user authentication`
- `fix(api): handle empty response`
